<TEI xmlns="http://www.tei-c.org/ns/1.0" xmlns:frus="http://history.state.gov/frus/ns/1.0"><text><body><div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1939-04-13T21:00:00-05:00" frus:doc-dateTime-min="1939-04-13T21:00:00-05:00" n="547" subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d547">
                            <note rend="inline" type="source">894.5151/133: Telegram</note>
                            <head><hi rend="italic">The Ambassador in Japan</hi> (<persName type="from"><hi rend="italic">Grew</hi></persName>) <hi rend="italic">to the <gloss type="to">Secretary of
                                    State</gloss></hi></head>
                            <opener>
                                <dateline rendition="#right"><placeName><hi rend="smallcaps">Tokyo</hi></placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1939-04-14T11:00:00+09:00">April 14, 1939—11
                                        a.m.</date><lb/>[Received April 14—1:10 a.m.]</dateline>
                            </opener>
                            <p>176. Department’s telegram No. 89, April 8, 3 [<hi rend="italic">1</hi>] p.m., deferred dollar remittances of American President
                                Lines. After consultation with the company’s representative we find
                                total awaiting remittance is approximately 390,000 yen. This has
                                been partly covered by permits through June. Accordingly
                                representations were made orally yesterday with a view to expediting
                                pending and future remittances.</p>
                            <closer><signed><hi rend="smallcaps">Grew</hi></signed></closer>
                        </div>
                        </body></text></TEI>